{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-8","id":"msg_01N9rFfzmH8GBEkpbubM6S62","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01SB2NJHskx7dvyCGzKLCmhg","name":"Bash","input":{"command":"read -r -d '' FINDINGS <<'EOF'\ningress-nginx Configuration Compliance Audit (READ-ONLY)\nNamespace: ingress-nginx | Controller: registry.k8s.io/ingress-nginx/controller:v1.14.1 | nginx 1.27.1\n\n== CONTROLLER ARGS (deploy/ingress-nginx-controller) ==\n[HIGH] Duplicate / conflicting flag: --watch-ingress-without-class is set TWICE\n  with contradictory values: \"=true\" (line 8) and \"=false\" appended at the end (last\n  occurrence wins in pflag, so EFFECTIVE value is FALSE). Conflicting duplicate flags are\n  a config-drift / change-management red flag and make controller intent ambiguous. With\n  the effective value false, Ingresses lacking an explicit ingressClassName/annotation are\n  NOT served, despite the manifest appearing to opt them in.\n[MED] --publish-status-address=localhost : status address pinned to localhost; Ingress\n  .status.loadBalancer will publish 'localhost' rather than a routable address — breaks\n  external status reporting / external-dns style consumers.\n[INFO] Standard args present: --election-id, --controller-class=k8s.io/ingress-nginx,\n  --ingress-class=nginx, --validating-webhook on :8443.\n\n== CONTROLLER CONFIGMAP (ingress-nginx/ingress-nginx-controller) ==\n[INFO] data is EMPTY (null) — no custom NGINX tuning applied (no proxy timeouts,\n  ssl-protocols, ssl-ciphers, hsts, proxy-body-size, etc.). Hardening directives such as\n  ssl-protocols (TLSv1.2/1.3 only), enable-modsecurity, hsts, server-tokens=false are\n  NOT configured — defaults in effect.\n\n== POD SECURITY / RELIABILITY ==\n[MED] securityContext.readOnlyRootFilesystem: false — root FS is writable (hardening gap).\n[MED] replicas: 1 — no high availability; single point of failure for ingress traffic.\n[MED] terminationGracePeriodSeconds: 0 — abrupt shutdown can drop in-flight connections\n  (no graceful drain), despite preStop /wait-shutdown hook.\n[LOW] automountServiceAccountToken: true.\n[LOW] hostPort 80/443 in use (node-level port binding).\n[INFO] Good baseline: runAsNonRoot=true, runAsUser=101, allowPrivilegeEscalation=false,\n  capabilities drop ALL (add only NET_BIND_SERVICE), seccompProfile RuntimeDefault.\n\n== INGRESS RESOURCES / EXPOSURE ==\n[HIGH] NO Ingress resources exist in the demo namespace (or any namespace: 'get ingress -A'\n  => none). The demo-app Deployment is running but has NO Service and NO Ingress — the app\n  is NOT actually exposed through the ingress controller, contradicting the documented\n  intent. Combined with watch-ingress-without-class effectively=false, any classless\n  Ingress added later would also be silently ignored.\n[INFO] IngressClass 'nginx' (controller k8s.io/ingress-nginx) present and is not the\n  cluster default (no ingressclass.kubernetes.io/is-default-class annotation).\n\n== LOGS ==\n[INFO] Controller healthy: backend reloaded, leader elected, validation webhook on :8443.\n  No TLS/cert or config-parse errors in recent logs.\n\nAUDIT SCOPE: read-only inspection only; no cluster resources were modified.\nEOF\nkubectl -n demo create configmap config-audit --from-literal=findings.txt=\"$FINDINGS\"\necho \"---verify---\"\nkubectl -n demo get configmap config-audit -o jsonpath='{.data.findings\\.txt}' | head -c 200; echo; echo \"bytes:\"; kubectl -n demo get configmap config-audit -o jsonpath='{.data.findings\\.txt}' | wc -c","description":"Create config-audit ConfigMap with findings"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":797,"cache_read_input_tokens":38595,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":797},"output_tokens":2,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management