{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-8","id":"msg_0149j4Q4bkJ22AyxdG7qRfA5","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The audit is complete. The `config-audit` ConfigMap now exists in the `demo` namespace with non-empty `findings.txt` (2,938 bytes), and no live resources were modified — only the audit artifact was created.\n\n## Audit summary\n\nI inspected the controller Deployment, ConfigMap, IngressClass, Ingress resources (cluster-wide), the demo namespace, and controller logs. Key findings documented:\n\n**HIGH**\n- **Duplicate/conflicting controller flag** — `--watch-ingress-without-class` is set twice with contradictory values: `=true` early in the args and `=false` appended at the end. In pflag the **last occurrence wins**, so the effective value is `false`, contradicting the apparent intent. Classic config-drift red flag.\n- **App not actually exposed** — `get ingress -A` returns none; the `demo-app` Deployment is running but has **no Service and no Ingress**, so it isn't routed through the controller at all, contrary to the stated setup.\n\n**MEDIUM**\n- `--publish-status-address=localhost` — Ingress status will publish a non-routable address.\n- `readOnlyRootFilesystem: false`, `replicas: 1` (no HA), `terminationGracePeriodSeconds: 0` (no graceful drain).\n\n**INFO / good baseline**\n- Controller ConfigMap `data` is empty — no TLS/HSTS/timeout hardening applied (defaults in effect).\n- Solid pod security baseline: `runAsNonRoot`, non-root UID, no privilege escalation, capabilities drop ALL (only NET_BIND_SERVICE), seccomp RuntimeDefault.\n- Controller healthy in logs; webhook on :8443; no errors.\n\nAll work was read-only inspection plus the single required ConfigMap creation in `demo`."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":2168,"cache_read_input_tokens":39392,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_toke